          "libraryTitle": "Multiple Choice",
          "action": {
            "library": "H5P.MultiChoice 1.16",
            "params": {
              "question": "<p>A patient experiences increased heart rate and dilated pupils during a sudden fright. Which division of the autonomic nervous system mediates this response, and from which spinal levels does it originate?</p>",
              "answers": [
                {
                  "text": "<div>Parasympathetic division; cranial nerves and sacral segments</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>The parasympathetic division mediates rest-and-digest responses such as slowing heart rate, not the fight-or-flight response.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Sympathetic division; thoracic and upper lumbar segments (T1–L2)</div>",
                  "correct": true,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>Correct. The sympathetic division drives the fight-or-flight response, producing tachycardia and mydriasis. It arises from spinal levels T1 through L2.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Somatic nervous system; cervical spinal segments</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>The somatic nervous system controls voluntary skeletal muscle movements, not involuntary cardiac and pupillary responses.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Sympathetic division; cranial nerves III, VII, IX, and X</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>These cranial nerves carry parasympathetic fibres, not sympathetic. The sympathetic division arises from thoracolumbar spinal levels.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                }
              ],
              "overallFeedback": [
                {
                  "from": 0,
                  "to": 50,
                  "feedback": "The fight-or-flight response is mediated by the sympathetic division, which arises from thoracic and upper lumbar spinal levels (T1–L2), not from cranial or sacral levels."
                },
                {
                  "from": 51,
                  "to": 100,
                  "feedback": "Well done. The sympathetic division, originating from T1–L2, activates the fight-or-flight response including tachycardia, mydriasis, and bronchodilatation."
                }
              ],
