          "height": 25,
          "libraryTitle": "Multiple Choice",
          "action": {
            "library": "H5P.MultiChoice 1.16",
            "params": {
              "question": "<p>Which of the following correctly distinguishes a sympathetic ganglion from a dorsal root ganglion?</p>",
              "answers": [
                {
                  "text": "<div>A sympathetic ganglion contains multipolar neurons with synapses, whereas a dorsal root ganglion contains pseudounipolar neurons without synapses</div>",
                  "correct": true,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>Correct. Sympathetic ganglia house multipolar motor neurons with preganglionic-to-postganglionic synapses. Dorsal root ganglia contain pseudounipolar sensory neurons and have no internal synapses.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>A sympathetic ganglion contains pseudounipolar neurons, whereas a dorsal root ganglion contains multipolar neurons</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>This is reversed. Dorsal root ganglia contain pseudounipolar sensory neurons, while sympathetic ganglia contain multipolar motor neurons.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>A dorsal root ganglion has synapses between pre- and postganglionic fibres, whereas a sympathetic ganglion has none</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>This is reversed. Sympathetic ganglia have synapses between preganglionic and postganglionic neurons. Dorsal root ganglia contain no synapses.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Both ganglia are structurally identical and differ only in their anatomical location</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>They differ significantly in neuron type (multipolar vs pseudounipolar), presence of synapses, and capsule prominence, not just location.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                }
              ],
              "overallFeedback": [
                {
                  "from": 0,
                  "to": 50,
                  "feedback": "Remember: sympathetic ganglia contain multipolar motor neurons with preganglionic–postganglionic synapses. Dorsal root ganglia contain pseudounipolar sensory neurons with no internal synapses."
                },
                {
                  "from": 51,
                  "to": 100,
                  "feedback": "Well done. The key differences are: sympathetic ganglia have multipolar neurons and synapses; dorsal root ganglia have pseudounipolar neurons and no synapses."
                }
              ],
